<h1>Debian-ARM Software Map</h1>

<h2>Intro</h2>

<p>The purpose of this document is to identify the sources of software
that will go into the <a href="/ports/arm/">Debian NetWinder
Port</a>.  This document is very new and probably quite
inaccurate.</p>

<h2>What groups are working on it?</h2>

<p>The primary work on getting Linux to work on the NetWinder is being
done by <a href="http://www.corelcomputer.com/">Corel Computer</a>
(CCC), based on the work of Russell King's <a
href="http://www.arm.uk.linux.org/">ARM Linux</a> port (kernel stuff
plus a.out RPMs for the Acorn) - with lots of help from the <a
href="http://www.oclug.on.ca/">Ottawa-Carleton Linux Users Group</a>
(OCLUG).</p>

<p>Corel and the OCLUG have set up <a
href="http://www.netwinder.org/">NetWinder.org</a> to facilitate
co-operation between them and the rest of the Open Source community.
And of course, there's us, the <a href="index">Debian
NetWinder porting project</a>.</p>

