<h2>Porting difficulties</h2>

<p>On the ARM architecture, all structs must be 32-bit aligned.
Normally, the Linux kernel would trap accesses that aren't 32-bit
aligned and work around it - but that has not yet been implemented in
the ARM Linux kernel.  San Mehat is working on a kernel trap handler
for this - it will be disabled by default, but can be turned on to
handle problem programs.</p>

<p>Also, the GNU tools will try to space out the bytes in C
structures to optimize for performance.  This can be a problem for
certain programs which expect a certain arrangement of bytes.  For
more info, read this:</p>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.netwinder.org/~brianbr/alignment.html">Brian Bray's ARM/NetWinder Structure Alignment FAQ</a>
</ul>


